SIMPLE: recoverable
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Recoverable
<hw>Re*cov"er*a*ble</hw> <pr>(-?*b'l)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[Cf. F.
<ets>recouvrable</ets>.]</ety> <def>Capable of being recovered or
regained; capable of being brought back to a former condition, as from
sickness, misfortune, etc.; obtainable from a debtor or possessor;
<as>as, the debt is <ex>recoverable</ex>; goods lost or sunk in the
ocean are not <ex>recoverable</ex>.</as></def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>A prodigal course⟦br⟧
Is like the sun's; but not, like his, <qex>recoverable</qex>.</q>
<rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>If I am <qex>recoverable</qex>, why am I thus?</q>
<rj><qau>Cowper.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p>-- <wordforms><wf>Re*cov"er*a*ble*ness</wf>,
<pos>n.</pos></wordforms>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Re coverance</ent>⟦br⟧
